<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16446] Parent repair sessions leak may lead to node long pauses</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16446</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ActiveRepairService&lt;/tt&gt; keeps  a map `parentRepairSessions`. If these sessions leak, that map can grow to a size when a node restarts &lt;tt&gt;ActiveRepairService.onRestart()&lt;/tt&gt; triggers a cleanup of sessions that can pause nodes in a cluster for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed solution is for repairs to cleanup these sessions on all nodes on completion by sending a CLEANUP message to involved nodes. Tests rely on a new &lt;tt&gt;parentRepairSessionsCount()&lt;/tt&gt; method on the parent repair sessions MBean to keep track of these.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
